text:
She has no problem packing her concerts with thousands of screaming fans all over the world.

But Rihanna turned her attention from singing to fashion on Sunday, as she headlined one of the most anticipated events of New York Fashion Week.

The Bajan-born beauty, 29, was perfectly sports-chic in a plunging sports jumper and striking stiletto boots, as she showed off her new Fenty x Puma collaboration atPark Avenue Armory.

Scroll down for video

Fit to bust! Rihanna turned her attention from singing to fashion on Sunday, as she headlined one of the most anticipated events of New York Fashion Week

Shut Up And Drive: The beauty, 29, was perfectly sports-chic in a plunging sports jumper and stiletto boots, as she showed off her new Fenty x Puma collaboration atPark Avenue Armory

The show saw the singer flaunt her impressive cleavage in a low-cut cardigan from the collection, which heavily drew inspiration from the clothing of racing car drivers.

Maintaining the sporty feel from head to toe, Rihanna teamed the top with striking green and leather trousers, and sky-high stilettos of matching hue.

Sweeping her hair into a tight bun, the songstress displayed her glowing skin to all - before she added a punky pair of rectangular sunglasses as she draped herself across the back of the motorbike, and playfully posed for fans.

Rockstar 101: Rih flashed the hand sign universally known to gesture rock and roll as she caught her lift

Ready to race: The singer looked tough in her biker-inspired ensemble as she posed with a bunch of professional bikers

Lets do this! Rihanna could not contain her excitement as she sped across the stage on the back of the bike, and blew kisses at fans

Fierce: Rihanna was effortlessy cool as she powered round the stage on the bike

Bad gal: Riri seemed to be basking in the added edge that the motorcycle exit came with

Capture the moment: Her driver wore a GoPro camera on his helmet to remember his gig

The Rockstar 101 singer appeared to be having the time of her life as she made a lap around the runway, driven by a professional BMX driver, before exiting after the models had walked the catwalk.

Models showing off Rihanna's collaboration with athletic wear giant Puma included Adriana Lima, Stella Maxwell and Joan Smalls.

Maxwell, who had been spotted earlier in the day hanging out with girlfriend Kristen Stewart, modeled the same boots that Rihanna proudly ripped from the runway as she presented her new line.

Victoria's Secret stunner Taylor Hill also added to the fray in a stunning black dress, while Cindy Crawford's daughter Kaia Gerber pounded the catwalk in her third ever runway show.

Suited and booted: Maintaining the sporty feel from head to toe, Rihanna teamed her saucy top with striking green and leather trousers, and sky-high stilettos of matching hue

Getting to Work: Backstage she hugged her motocross pal who drove her down the catwalk

Pucker up! The singer playfully pouted for the crowds after the debut of her collection

Smile and wave! Rihanna appeared completely relaxed as she posed for fans

Pucker up: Her face was painted with cosmetics from her new makeup line Fenty Beauty

Expanding: In the past year, Rihanna has tried her hand at acting, fashion and cosmetic ventures

Rihanna herself was also seen keeping busy backstage, and making final touches to the collection ahead of its big Fashion Week debut.

Stars eager to get a glimpse of Riri's new collection included model Ashley Graham and rappers Big Sean and Cardi B.

Clearly excited for the collection's catwalk appearance, Rihanna went live on Instagram to broadcast the event to her 56.5 million fans worldwide.

'I'm going live tonight so y'all could show up uninvited,' she wrote before the festivities.

Glowing: Rihanna flashed plenty of her smooth skin and her toned midriff in the striking sports-chic ensemble as she helped the models backstage

Ripped from the runway: Stella Maxwell modeled the same boots Rihanna wore to the event

Taking her lap: Adriana Lima showed off this blue racing-inspired bodysuit, playing on the theme of high-speed style that Rihanna echoed with her motorbike entrance

Fierce: Joan Smalls struck a confident stance in this black, blue and red suit paired with blue heels

Leading ladies: Kaia Gerber (L) strutted her stuff during her third ever catwalk appearance, while Taylor Hill (R) showed off her famously slender frame in a slinky black dress

Sports luxe: Taylor teamed the dress with a waterproof green rain mac and heeled flip flops

Swim chic: The collection also included plenty of swimwear, including a striking pink and navy bikini and a bright cobalt blue swimsuit with a zip down the front

Vibrant: One model teamed a slinky navy swim suit with bright yellow boots

Underwear as outerwear: Rihanna put a quirky twist on a traditional pair of panties, adding mesh detailing to them, as well as a cheeky 'wet' waistband

Flip flopped: The singer-turned-designer played with juxtoposing styles on the runway, mixing glamorous ensembles such as this all-black look with more casual elements, like flip flops

Dress down: Much of the runway collection focused on urban-inspired streetwear, with cropped hoodies featuring throughout much of the show

Androgyny: Styles that are typically associated with men, such as baggy, low-slung shorts and sweats, were given a more feminine feel

Let's hear it for the boys: Men also strutted the catwalk in an array of waterproof wear

That's a wrap! The models did one last catwalk run together as they finished their appearances at the show

The Work singer has been hard at work with projects outside of her ultra-successful music career.

Last week she launched Fenty Beauty featuring 40 shades of foundation at Sephora and Harvey Nichols.

'You knoooowwww it!' the Women's Marcher gushed on Instagram last week.

'Gotta represent for my girls and we come in all shades! Especially my brown sisters...been left out too many times in the makeup world!'

Leggy lady: Cardi B flashed her leggy frame in high-waisted denim shorts and an orange padded jacket as she took her place on the FROW

Doing it for the Graham: Meanwhile Ashley Graham attended the event as a spectator, having just walked a runway for Prubal Gurung moments before

In the nude: Ashley slipped her famous curves into a sexy PVC midi dress, with a striking mesh and air-tex bodice

Feeling blue? Joan Small and Adriana Lima dazzled as they posed after the event

Radaint: Kaia Gerber proved her natural beauty as she got ready backstage

Fierce: The model's striking features were clear for all to see as she posed for cameras

Playful: Meanwhile Adriana Lima flashed a few playful poses at the camera as she prepared for her catwalk appearance
title: Rihanna gives a flash of cleavage at NYFW show
